15:
Terrible things will happen to those who try to conceal from me, Yahweh,\q2 the evil things that they plan to do;
\q1 they do those deeds in the darkness
\q2 and they think, 'Yahweh certainly cannot see us;
\q2 he cannot know what we are doing!'


\q1

18:
At that time, deaf people will be able to hear;\q2 they will be able to hear when someone reads from a book;
\q1 and blind people will be able to see;
\q2 they will be able to see things when it is gloomy and even when it is dark.
\q1

22:
That is why Yahweh, who rescued Abraham, says about the people of Israel,\q1 "My people will no longer be ashamed;
\q2 no longer will they show on their faces that they are ashamed.
\q1
